definitions.definition: The part of the flower stalk ( peduncle or pedicel ) to which the floral parts are attached ; a thalamus , a torus .

subdefinitions.definition: A condensed rachis of a capitate or umbellate inflorescence at the end of the peduncle, to which all of the florets or pedicels are attached.

definitions.definition: A structure at the end of a branch of an alga containing conceptacles ( reproductive organs ).
An organ that receives and holds a secretion .
A contact device installed at an outlet for the connection of an attachment plug (typically by receiving the plug's prongs ) to supply portable appliances or equipment .

secondary_definitions: ( botany ) The part of the flower stalk ( peduncle or pedicel ) to which the floral parts are attached ; a thalamus , a torus .
